To run the analysis in lxplus:
===============================

0) Modifications:
------------------

Modify the following files, if needed:

* HPlusHadronic_x.txt	rates & uncertainties for mH=x
* input_luminosity	luminosity


1) compile the modified LandS software
------------------------------------------------------------------------

NOTE: do not give "cmsenv" command before compiling LandS

mkdir LandS_AN
tar -xzf /afs/cern.ch/user/t/tlampen/public/LandS_AN_110610.tgz -C LandS_AN
cd LandS_AN/LandS
setenv ROOTSYS "/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/app/releases/ROOT/5.28.00/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-dbg/root"
setenv PATH "$ROOTSYS/bin:$PATH"
setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH "$ROOTSYS/lib"
gmake clean; gmake all;
cd ../..

Sidenote:
 This LandS version is modified by Sasha, and copied from his directory 10.6.2011:
 cp /afs/cern.ch/user/a/anikiten/scratch0/LandS/LandSmod/LandS.tgz .
 Instructions of how to use LandS are here:
 http://cmsdoc.cern.ch/~anikiten/cms-higgs/LandsInstructions.txt


2) run LandS (takes 20-30 min; you may skip this and directly make 
the plots with the presaved values if you want don't want 
to run LandS again)
-------------------------------------------------------------

./script_run_LandS

*As a result, files output_LandS_xxx are (re)generated


3) run the ROOT analysis to obtain Br limit (mH,Br)
---------------------------------------------------

root -l -b -q brlimit.C

*As a result, the br limit plot brlimits.png/eps is generated


4) run the python analysis to obtain MSSM limit (mH,tanB)
---------------------------------------------------------

cmsenv
./mssmLimit.py

*As a result, the tanB limit plot mssmLimit.png is generated
